history.content:
DFT and Fourier Series is probably the most important. You should be somewhat comfortable with it by the end of EE 16B, but they are both reviewed (and introduced more rigorously) in EE 120. 

Knowing how to make Bode plots is also important, that too is reviewed in EE 120.

All the material from the robotics and control theory unit is also pretty helpful, many iterations of EE 120 will spend a some time on state-space representations, feedback controllers, controllability, stability, etc. but go through it quickly as they assume knowledge from EE16B. 

Most important is just having good linear algebra background and mathematical maturity.

children.subject: Tbh EE120 should be a prereq for 16B because the class starts from foundations and builds up. As long as you are reasonably comfortable with dealing with sequences, series, and integrals, you should be able to take EE 120.
